blocks.name: ragcom
blocks.content: Commutative rule for right angles. Theorem 8.2 of [Schwabhauser] p. 57. (Contributed by Thierry Arnoux, 25-Aug-2019.)

  -| wceq(c6, cfv(citv, c3))
  -| wceq(c7, cfv(clng, c3))
  -| wceq(c8, cfv(cmir, c3))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c3, cstrkg))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c2, c4))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c1, c4))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c0, c4))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(cs3(c2, c1, c0), cfv(crag, c3)))
} = {
  mpbird(w0, wcel(cs3(c0, c1, c2), cfv(crag, c3)), wceq(co(c0, c5, c2), co(c0, c5, cfv(cfv(c8, c1), c2))))

  mpbid(w0, wceq(co(c2, c5, c0), co(c2, c5, cfv(cfv(c8, c1), c0))), wcel(cs3(c2, c1, c0), cfv(crag, c3)))
  israg(c2, c1, c0, c3, c5, c8, c4, c6, c7, w0)
  miriso(cfv(c8, c1), cfv(cfv(c8, c1), c0), c5, c2, c4, c3, c6, c7, c8, c1, w0)
  mircl(cfv(c8, c1), c0, c4, c3, c5, c6, c7, c8, c1, w0)
  oveq1d(cfv(cfv(c8, c1), cfv(cfv(c8, c1), c0)), c5, cfv(cfv(c8, c1), c2), c0, w0)

thm isperp(setvar s0, setvar s1, setvar s2, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, class c4, class c5, class c6, wff w0) {
  |- wi(w0, wb(wbr(c0, cfv(cperpg, c1), c2), wrex(s0, cin(c0, c2), wral(s1, c0, wral(s2, c2, wcel(cs3(cv(s1), cv(s0), cv(s2)), cfv(crag, c1)))))))
  -| wceq(c3, cfv(cbs, c1))
  -| wceq(c4, cfv(cds, c1))
  -| wceq(c5, cfv(citv, c1))
  -| wceq(c6, cfv(clng, c1))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c1, cstrkg))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c0, crn(c6)))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c2, crn(c6)))
  -| diffss(s0, s1)
  -| diffss(s0, s2)
  -| diffss(s1, s2)

  -| diffsc(s0, c1)
  -| diffsc(s0, c2)

  -| diffsc(s1, c2)

  -| diffsc(s2, c2)

  -| diffsw(s2, w0)
} = {
  a1ii(wi(w0, wb(wbr(c0, cfv(cperpg, c1), c2), wrex(s0, cin(c0, c2), wral(s1, c0, wral(s2, c2, wcel(cs3(cv(s1), cv(s0), cv(s2)), cfv(crag, c1))))))), wceq(c3, cfv(cbs, c1)))

blocks.name: foot
blocks.content: From a point ` C ` outside of a line ` A ` , there exists a unique point ` x ` on ` A ` such that ` ( C L x ) ` is perpendicular to ` A ` . That point is called the foot from ` C ` on ` A ` . Theorem 8.18 of [Schwabhauser] p. 60. (Contributed by Thierry Arnoux, 19-Oct-2019.)

blocks.name: colperpex
blocks.content: In dimension 2 and above, on a line ` ( A L B ) ` there is always a perpendicular ` P ` from ` A ` on a given plane (here given by ` C ` , in case ` C ` does not lie on the line). Theorem 8.21 of [Schwabhauser] p. 63. (Contributed by Thierry Arnoux, 20-Nov-2019.)
blocks.origin:
thm colperpex(setvar s0, setvar s1, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, class c4, class c5, class c6, class c7, wff w0) {
  |- wi(w0, wrex(s0, c0, wa(wbr(co(c1, c2, cv(s0)), cfv(cperpg, c3), co(c1, c2, c4)), wrex(s1, c0, wa(wo(wcel(cv(s1), co(c1, c2, c4)), wceq(c1, c4)), wcel(cv(s1), co(c5, c6, cv(s0))))))))

blocks.name: midex
blocks.content: Existence of the midpoint, part Theorem 8.22 of [Schwabhauser] p. 64. Note that this proof requires a construction in 2 dimensions or more, i.e. it does not prove the existence of a midpoint in dimension 1, for a geometry restricted to a line. (Contributed by Thierry Arnoux, 25-Nov-2019.)
